{"key":"processedPost-12384370","value":{"id":12384370,"first":12377916,"last":12384380,"when":1271175255,"utime":"04/13/10 07:14 PM","content":"I don't grow species which require a casing layer, so no.&nbsp; <br /><br />Late casing seems to be about the same as applying a sheet of wax paper to hold humidity.&nbsp; If the substrate dries out, you can simply pour water around the edges of the substrate, and let it soak in.&nbsp; As I said above, I saw no benefit to using a casing layer with cubensis, and plenty of reasons not to, such as the extra vector of contamination that isn't present with uncased bulk substrates.<br />RR","title":"Re: half and half","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}